e industry's survival. In outlining this archive's contents, Finkelstein shows how mills, which she conceptualizes as lively ruins, become a lens through which to challenge, reimagine, and alter ways of thinking about the past, present, and future in Mumbai and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aArchitecture, DomesticzIndiazMumbai. 0aTenement houseszIndiazMumbai. 0aTextile industryzIndiazMumbaixHistory. 0aTextile workersxHousingzIndiazMumbai. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478004608zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478004608423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478004608.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles